ce religion. Education is a social institution, and it should account for the religious diversity within Toronto. Health is also a social institution, and there are prayer rooms within hospitals. A simple prayer room that is multi-faith would be great in every school and would respect the diversity within the TDSB to which we in Canada and Toronto love to brag about....We are so multi-cultural. There should never be discussion about God in a classroom, but there should be respect for those who do believe in God. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="825" language="en" documentId="1531" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Jethwa118" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/tempers-flare-over-prayer-in-schools-1.1104775" topic="prayer-in-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="1531" notes="" title="Tempers flare over prayer in schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="825"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>